## Description
The **Publish Documents (Pvideo Designer) **task allows to create personalized videos (Pvideos) on the Pvideo Designer platform, and returns the Purl.

> Note

For more information on the structure of the input file, see [XML Input File Structure for Doxee Platform 3 Native Tasks](/doxee-platform/docs/xml-input-file-structure-for-doxee-platform-3-native-tasks) (section **Pvideo production Pvideo Designer**).

> Note

Access to projects and mapping schemas from the task's configuration dialog is granted only to users with proper permissions.

See [How to Integrate with Pvideo Designer from Doxee Platform 3](https://code.doxee.com/confluence/display/DP3ID/How%2Bto%2BIntegrate%2Bwith%2BPvideo%2BDesigner%2Bfrom%2BDoxee%2BPlatform%2B3) for instructions on how to request access.

## Configuration
- In the **Alias **field, enter the name of the task to be displayed in the workflow.

- Toggle the "**Use configuration from input**" option to enable override from the input XML file.

> Important

When enabled, **PROJECT **and **MAPPING **must be provided in the input XML (see [XML Input File Structure for Doxee Platform 3 Native Tasks](/doxee-platform/docs/xml-input-file-structure-for-doxee-platform-3-native-tasks)). The task will fail if either of these tags is missing.

- In the **Project **field, select the name of the Pvideo project to use for the production.

- In the **Mapping **field, select the name of the Pvideo mapping to use for the production.

- *(optional) *In the **Storyboard **field, select the name of the storyboard to use for the production.

> Note

The storyboard selection is optional. However, if a dynamic storyboard is not configured in the mapping schema, it must be provided either in the task configuration or in the XML input.

## Output branches
The **Publish Documents (Pvideo Designer) **task's output may be connected by the following branch types:

**Branch type**

**Mandatory**

**Description**

**Default**

Default branch containing successfully produced documents.

**Discard**

Branch containing discarded communications.

## Error codes
The following error codes may be associated with a discarded communication; additional information is available in the task's execution logs.

**Error code**

**Description**

CONFIGURATION_ERR OR

The user configuration contains errors.

DP3_BRIDGE_ERROR

An error occurred while attempting to retrieve the API key for the account.

GENERIC_ERROR

A generic unexpected error occurred.

EMPTY_RESPONSE

A generic error occurred, and it was not possible to retrieve more details.

NO_COMMUNICATIONS

The provided input does not include any communication.

PARSER_ERROR

The communication does not adhere to the expected schema and could not be parsed.

PVIDEO_DESIGNER_E RROR

An error was returned by the Pvideo Designer APIs. It may be a temporary issue, or there might be something wrong with the provided input data.
